The article discusses President Donald J. Trump's proposal for a merit-based immigration system in the United States. The President believes that the current system should be replaced with one that admits skilled individuals who are willing to work, contribute to society, and love and respect the country. The proposal aims to fully secure the border and transition to a competitive, merit-based system. The President emphasizes the importance of border security as the foundation of a functional immigration system. The proposal also prioritizes merit over chance, ensuring that American workers are protected. Additionally, the President's plan aims to increase American competitiveness in attracting and retaining talented individuals by adopting effective point systems used by other countries.